Package cipher

Class NGramAnalyser

java.lang.Object
cipher.NGramAnalyser
public class NGramAnalyser
extends java.lang.Object
A class that is capable of counting the number of given strings of length n that occur in a given string.
Author:
Max Wood

    • NgramAnalysis

      public java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Double> NgramAnalysis​(int n, java.lang.String text, boolean isSpaced)
      Creates a map of ngrams in target text.
      Parameters:
      n - Integer length of the ngrams to be found in the text.
      text - String to be analysed.
      isSpaced - Boolean whether or not the text contains spaces already.
      Returns:
      TreeMap of all ngrams and fraction of text they represent.

    • kasiskiBase

      public java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Integer> kasiskiBase​(int n, java.lang.String text)
      Creates a map of ngrams and frequencies in unspaced target text.
      Parameters:
      n - Integer length of the ngrams to be found in the text.
      text - String to be analysed.
      Returns:
      TreeMap of all length n strings in the text, in order to look for repeats.

    • computeScore

      public double computeScore​(int n, java.lang.String text, boolean perGram)
      Computes the log score for the ngrams present in the analysed text. Higher is better.
      Parameters:
      n - The length of the nGrams we wish to test for.
      text - The input text to be analysed.
      perGram - Whether or not we want an adjusted score based on the length of text, in order to compare texts of varying lengths.
      Returns:
      A double representing the total score of the text. Higher is better.
